    "body": "Currently tests double escape moving between Python => JVM => SQL parser\r\n\r\nUsing DataFrame API, or SQL expressions with raw Python/Scala strings is more intuitive/readable. Here are a few ways to generate a plan  with the expression `split(a#235, [\\\\.], 2)`\r\n\r\nspark-sql REPL:\r\n\r\n ```sql\r\nSELECT split(a, r\"[\\\\.]\", 2) FROM df;\r\n```\r\n\r\nPython REPL:\r\n\r\n```Python\r\n\r\ndf.selectExpr(r'split(a, \"[\\\\\\\\.]\", 2)')\r\n\r\ndf.selectExpr(r'split(a, r\"[\\\\.]\", 2)')\r\n\r\nimport pyspark.sql.functions as f\r\ndf.select(f.split(\"a\", r\"[\\\\.]\", 2))\r\n```\r\n\r\nScala REPL:\r\n\r\n```Scala\r\ndf.selectExpr(\"\"\"split(a, r\"[\\\\.]\" ,2)\"\"\")\r\n\r\nimport org.apache.spark.sql.{functions => f}\r\ndf.select(f.split($\"a\", raw\"[\\\\.]\", 2))\r\n```\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @gerashegalov in https://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids/pull/8273#discussion_r1192863397_\r\n            ",
